{
  "stem": "33.3",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So there were actually two epidemics in camp.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The first one was a very mild scarlet fever epidemic, and they took people away and nobody came back.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we knew where they went.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So when they took me away with the measles, my friends thought that I go to the same destination.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So they cried.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And-- but there was  nothing they could do, because measles were like very visible all over my body, and they couldn't hide me.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I was taken to a different camp, a small camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Not where the main hospital was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But I knew through the grapevine that my cousin, who is 17 years older than I am, a practicing physician in private life, she was in this camp, working in this hospital, as a doctor-- a prisoner, of course-- as a doctor.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The only reason she survived was because when that transport arrived from a different city, also in Transylvania, but a larger city, a university town, they asked doctors to stand aside when they arrived at Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So as a good, law-abiding citizen, as we all were, she stood aside.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Her only child, a little boy, who turned 7 years old during that journey to Auschwitz, went with my cousin's parents, with the boy's grandparents, to the left.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "If they didn't need doctors that day, of course, she would have gone with her child to the gas chamber.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When I got to the hospital, the pediatrician, also from the same city where my cousin was from, examined me.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was-- I told her that my cousin is there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So she came running, and she was relieved that at that point they didn't take people with measles to the gas chamber.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There was already a room established for people who had the measles.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
